On Mon, 19 Apr 1999, Craig Whitmore wrote:
> The bios when you set up IDE drives only gives an option of 2 IDE channels..
> How can
> you set the others up? Or an I asking a stupid question?
You dont. The kernel autodetects. The only problem here is that you
couldn't boot off one of those later controlers.. In fact, I often turn
off IDE drives in bios (cept boot drive) because Linux's autodetect code
does better then many bioses.
